  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Intervention multisectorielle, Nord Kivu</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed intervention is to provide an urgent rapid response to the identification of movements of populations affected by the violence of armed conflicts in Walikale territory, namely the health zones of Kibua and Pinga and the territory of Masisi in the health zones of Mweso and Masisi. As part of its emergency response and strong experience with the PUNC, AAH proposes an intervention scheme which will revolve around 5 steps: escalation alerts and coordination (direct information to the AAH team and inormation via humanitarian partners), rapid assessment of needs (to confirm the movement of population and identify the number of households/persons concerned within 3-4 days),  selection of beneficiaries (target priority populations will be chldren under 5 and preganant and nursing women) integrated or sectoral intervention (the project has a mulisectoral approach and concerns nutrition sectors, WaSH, and livelihood and shelter provisions), and follow up activities and investigations of post distribution (Post distribution follow-up surveys will be held in each sector of intervention).</narrative>
  </description>
